   <p>For more on the business that GW entrusted to Fielding Lewis before he left for Philadelphia, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0342" class="document">Lewis to GW, 14 Nov. 1775</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0181" class="document">4 Feb. 1776</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0307" class="document">6 Mar. 1776</a>. In the David Library of the American Revolution is a brief account with Lewis, certified by GW on 27 April 1775 (<span class="ref-rep">PWacD</span>: Sol Feinstone Collection, on deposit <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ American Philosophical Society, Philadelphia, Pa. ]">PPAmP</span>).</p>

